               <p>JAMES PETTIT SNELL. I live in Aldermanbury. On the night of the 4th of July, at a quarter-past ten o'clock, I was in <placeName id="t18320705-141-crimeloc753">Cheapside, opposite Gutter-lane</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18320705-141-crimeloc753" type="placeName" value="Cheapside, opposite Gutter-lane"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18320705-141-crimeloc753" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320705-141-off751 t18320705-141-crimeloc753"></join> - I felt a man's hand at my pocket, and called out Halloo! the prisoner, who was very near me, immediately ran across Cheapside, and down Gutter-lane - I followed him; I saw him throw down my handkerchief about half way across Cheapside - a friend took it up, and gave it me; I took the prisoner in Gutter-lane.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18320705-141-person1230">
                  ROBERT 
                  STANFORD
               <interp inst="t18320705-141-person1230" type="surname" value="STANFORD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320705-141-person1230" type="given" value="ROBERT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320705-141-person1230" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was with the prosecutor. I saw the prisoner throw down the handkerchief; I took it up, and took it to the watch-house - I gave it to the officer.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18320705-141-person1231">
                  GEORGE 
                  WILLIAMS
               <interp inst="t18320705-141-person1231" type="surname" value="WILLIAMS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320705-141-person1231" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320705-141-person1231" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer. I received the prisoner and this handkerchief.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I heard the alarm - two or three young men ran down Gutter-lane: I ran after them, but I am innocent.</p>
               <p>The prisoner received a good character.</p>
